"1. The "Email Domain" Extractor (String/Parsing)
The Goal: Take an email address (e.g., j.smith@google.com) and return only the domain (google.com).

The Challenge: It has to find the "@" symbol, regardless of where it is, and grab everything to the right.

The Expected Logic: SUBSTR({email}, INSTR({email}, '@') + 1)
Or (Modern Regex): REGEXP_SUBSTR({email}, '@(.*)$', 1, 1, NULL, 1)

2. The "Years & Months" Experience (Advanced Date Math)
The Goal: Calculate how long a customer has been with you in a readable format, like: "5 Years, 3 Months".

The Challenge: Simple subtraction gives you days. The bot must calculate the floor of years and the remainder of months.

The Expected Logic: TRUNC(MONTHS_BETWEEN(SYSDATE, {datecreated}) / 12) || ' Years, ' || TRUNC(MOD(MONTHS_BETWEEN(SYSDATE, {datecreated}), 12)) || ' Months'

