'<div style="width: 100px; border: 1px solid #ccc; height: 10px;"><div style="width: ' || {percentcomplete} || 'px; background-color: ' || (CASE WHEN {percentcomplete} < 50 THEN 'red' ELSE 'green' END) || '; height: 10px;"></div></div>'

4. The "Fiscal Year Offset" (Accounting Logic)
The Goal: Many companies have a Fiscal Year that starts in July, not January. Given a date, return the "Fiscal Year" integer (e.g., 08/01/2025 should return 2026).

The Challenge: Standard TO_CHAR(date, 'YYYY') will give you 2025. The bot must add 6 months before extracting the year.

The Expected Logic: TO_CHAR(ADD_MONTHS({trandate}, 6), 'YYYY')

